<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-27T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2457: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-27T19:00:00+01:00">October 27, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 27—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>28. Your 25, October 26, 5 p.m. I have communicated substance of this
                                telegram to <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName>. He was
                                happy to hear the news it contains and stated that the Council
                                committee when it learns of it will appreciate highly the successful
                                results which the Neutral Commission has obtained. <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> asks whether he may assume
                                that in due course the President of the Neutral Commission will
                                communicate this information formally to the President of the
                                Council so that the latter may impart it to his colleagues on the
                                Committee of Three and ultimately to the Council itself.</p>
                            <p>Please instruct.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>